      "body": "### Reason for requesting the library\n\nHibernate Processor is a standard Java annotation processor which produces the Jakarta Persistence static metamodel which validates queries at compilation time. The fields within the class are populated using reflection at runtime.\n\nWould it be possible to include generated types in the graalvm reachability metadata to allow reflection? These can be identified by the StaticMetamodel annotation.\n\nExample generated class\n```\n/**\n * Static metamodel for {@link com.domain.User}\n **/\n@StaticMetamodel(User.class)\n@Generated(\"org.hibernate.processor.HibernateProcessor\")\npublic abstract class User_ {\n\n\t/**\n\t * @see #status\n\t **/\n\tpublic static final String STATUS = \"status\";\n\n\t/**\n\t * Static metamodel for attribute {@link com.domain.User#status}\n\t **/\n\tpublic static volatile SingularAttribute<User, String> status;\n\n}\n```",
