  10527:<p>We&#8217;re going to learn more about Hibernate Processor in the next chapter.</p>
  10533:<h2 id="generator"><a class="anchor" href="#generator"></a>7. Compile-time tooling</h2>
  10536:<p>The <em>static metamodel generator</em> is a standard part of JPA.
  10537:We&#8217;ve actually already seen its handiwork in the code examples <a href="#main-hibernate">earlier</a>: it&#8217;s the author of the class <code>Book_</code>, which contains the static metamodel of the <a href="#book">entity class</a> <code>Book</code>.</p>
  10540:<p>Hibernate comes with an annotation processor which does much more than just this.
  10559:<div id="metamodel-generator" class="sidebarblock">
  10561:<div class="title">Hibernate Processor</div>
  10563:<p><a href="https://hibernate.org/orm/processor/">Hibernate Processor</a>, the annotation processor formerly known as the Metamodel Generator, began its life as a code generator for what JPA calls a <a href="https://jakarta.ee/specifications/persistence/3.2/jakarta-persistence-spec-3.2#a6072"><em>static metamodel</em></a>.
  10569:Back when Java&#8217;s annotation processing API was brand spankin' new, the static metamodel for JPA was proposed by Gavin King for inclusion in JPA 2.0, as a way to achieve type safety in the nascent criteria query API.
  10571:Tools did not, at the time, feature robust support for annotation processors.
  10577:<p>But time has been kind to the static metamodel.
  10580:The static metamodel itself is undeniably useful and elegant.</p>
  10584:Since Hibernate 6.3 the Processor has started taking on a much bigger role.
  10588:<p>Now, you still don&#8217;t have to use the Hibernate Processor with Hibernate—the APIs we just mentioned still also accept plain strings—but we find that it works well with Gradle and integrates smoothly with our IDE, and the advantage in type-safety is compelling.</p>
  10600:<p>We&#8217;ve already seen how to set up the annotation processor in the <a href="#hello-hibernate">Gradle build</a> we saw earlier.
  10601:For more details on how to integrate the Hibernate Processor, check out the <a href="https://docs.hibernate.org/orm/7.2/userguide/html_single/Hibernate_User_Guide.html#tooling-modelgen">Static Metamodel Generator</a> section in the User Guide.</p>
  10608:<h3 id="static-metamodel"><a class="anchor" href="#static-metamodel"></a>7.1. The static metamodel</h3>
  10610:<p>We&#8217;ve already seen several ways to use the JPA static metamodel.
  10705:<p>Hibernate Processor allows <em>statically-typed</em> access to elements of the JPA <code>Metamodel</code>. But the <code>Metamodel</code> is also accessible in a "reflective" way, via the <code>EntityManagerFactory</code>.</p>
  10722:<p>The JPA static metamodel for an entity also contains members representing the named queries and named entity graphs declared by <code>@NamedQuery</code>, <code>@NamedNativeQuery</code>, and <code>@NamedEntityGraph</code> annotations of the entity class.</p>
  10778:<p>Actually, Hibernate Processor doesn&#8217;t require that such annotations be applied to the entity class itself, as we <a href="#organizing-persistence">already saw earlier</a>.</p>
  10786:So now let&#8217;s see what else Hibernate Processor can do for us.</p>
